comments:
Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Kenwyn Rural and Kea. 
    See also Table 2, note (d).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Tregorney.

Abolished 1894 and divided between the separate parishes of Kenwyn 
    Urban and Kenwyn Rural.

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Kenwyn Rural and Tregavethan. 
    See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Kenwyn. Abolished 
    1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Kenwyn, Chacewater and Truro.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Kenwyn in Truro Municipal 
    Borough. Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Truro.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of St. Michael 
    Penkevil.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of St. Michael 
    Penkevil.

Renamed 5.10.1982 to become the parish of St. Newlyn East. See 
    also Table 2, note (c).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Gerrans.

Abolished 1894 and divided between the separate parishes of St. 
    Clement Urban and St. Clement Rural.

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of St. Clement Rural and 
    St. Erme. See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of St. Clement. 
    Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Truro and St. Clement.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of St. Clement in Truro 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Truro.
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Truro.

Created 5.10.1982 by renaming the parish of Newlyn. See also Table 
    2, note (d).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Kenwyn.

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Kenwyn Urban, St. Clement 
    Urban, St. Mary, St. Clement Rural and Kenwyn Rural. See also Table 2, note 
    (d).
